This paper deals with the challenges of training multi-modal networks, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses overfitting and optimization strategies, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper mentions acoustic event detection, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques for fine-grained sport classification, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
